<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Hexadecimal #colors</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>To specify more than just words for colors, you can specify the hexadecimal color, which looks something like #0FA.  <a href='http://www.htmlgoodies.com/tutorials/colors/article.php/3478951'>Look here</a> for more info.  The basic idea is that the first number mean how much red, the next how much blue, and the last much green in hexadecimal.  (e.g. #f00 means all red and no blue/green and #999 means gray)</p>
